<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
        <title>CSS Test: 'Border-radius' applied to element with 'display' set to 'table-caption'.</title>
        <link href="http://www.microsoft.com/" rel="author" title="Microsoft" />
        <link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-background/#border-radius" rel="help" />
        <meta content="" name="flags" />
        <meta content="When 'border-radius' is applied to an element with 'displaye: table-caption' it produces rounded corners." name="assert" />
        <style type="text/css">
            #caption
            {
                border: solid green;
                border-radius: 10px;
                display: table-caption;
                height: 1in;
                width: 1in;
            }
            #table
            {
                display: table;
            }
            #row
            {
                display: table-row;
            }
            #cell
            {
                display: table-cell;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is a box with rounded corners below.</p>
        <div id="table">
            <div id="caption"></div>
            <div id="row">
                <div id="cell"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    
</body></html>